# Cursor Rules for This Repository

Always read before coding:
- AGENTS.md
- docs/software-overview.md
- docs/limits.md

Execution rules:
- Stay within docs/limits.md boundaries.
- Keep scope tight; avoid unrelated refactors.
- State assumptions when requirements are incomplete.
- Prefer minimal, durable, testable fixes.

Quality and safety:
- Run impacted checks/tests.
- Do not expose secrets or sensitive data.
- Include privacy/compliance review when personal data is involved.
- If request conflicts with limits, stop and ask for explicit approval.

Issue workflow:
- Use docs/issues epic-folder structure and templates.
- Include privacy checklist when applicable.
- Use `work_id` format `WK-YYYYMMDD-<short-slug>` in planning docs and commit messages.

Session close (mandatory at each stage):
- Update `handoff.md`.
- Add short lesson to `docs/napkin-lessons.md`.
- Follow `docs/workflows/session-close.md`.
